PORTFOLIO

Rubik's Cube

A functioning, fully animated Rubik's Cube developed using C++ and OpenGL. Featuring textures, colour rendering through a lighting shader and sound.

Project on GitHub!

2D Level Editor

A tool to create and edit levels for a 2D platformer using tilesets. Developed in C++.

Project on GitHub!

Algorithmic Dungeon Level Generator

A Unity project to procedurally generate a Dungeon Crawler level. It features modular scripts making use of Unity's Scene Manager that can expanded within the project, or implemented in other projects.

Project on GitHub!

Ad Astra

A Game Dev Week Unity project where I did the UI programming and part of the Game Design.

Project on GitHub!

War Diaries WWII

An Unreal Engine VR Project developed for an interactive museum exhibition portraying a scene from a diary written during the second world war.

Project on GitHub!

ABOUT ME

Hi there, I'm Ben and I like playing and making video games! Besides that I also enjoy anything fantasy, be it books, shows, or movies. My dream is to one day get two large dogs and spoil them senseless!

I got my Bachelor of Computer Science from the Trier University of Applied Sciences. My education there revolved around video game production and I am now looking for my entry into the games industry.
